From 58479d3078c3c7553e0a09287da2c292ac94bb27 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anuj Gupta <anuj1072538@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 14:32:17 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] io_dmabuf: drop resv lock requirement from map release path
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

io_dmabuf_map_release_work() was taking the dma-buf reservation lock
around the unmap call. dma_buf_unmap_attachment() does not require the
reservation lock — only dma_buf_map_attachment() asserts dma_resv_held()
for dynamic attachments. The lock was an unnecessary constraint carried
over from the map side of the protocol.

The consequence was a deadlock: KFD restore holds the BO reservation lock
via drm_exec for the entire duration of BO validation + GPU VM page table
update. During that window it calls amdgpu_sync_wait() to wait for GPU
fences. The token fence (at DMA_RESV_USAGE_WRITE) is collected by
amdgpu_sync_resv() and ends up in that wait. io_dmabuf_map_release_work
signals the fence before trying to take the resv, so amdgpu_sync_wait()
can be unblocked. But with the resv required for unmap, the work item
then immediately blocks on the lock that KFD restore holds, and if KFD
restore is also waiting for a MOVE fence that depends on the token fence,
the result is a live dependency cycle that keeps both tasks blocked for
the hung-task timeout period.

Fix: remove the dma_resv_lock/unlock pair from io_dmabuf_map_release_work
and remove the corresponding dma_resv_assert_held() from
nvme_dmabuf_token_unmap(). The release work now signals the fence and
completes the unmap without acquiring any lock, eliminating the contention
with KFD restore.

The dma_buf_unmap_attachment() call tears down the NVMe device's IOMMU
mapping for the buffer. This is safe without the resv because:
- NVMe DMA has already stopped (percpu refs drained to zero, fence signal
  is the proof).
- The IOMMU entries being torn down belong to NVMe's attachment and are
  independent of the GPU's IOMMU mappings used by any concurrent blit.
- A concurrent io_dmabuf_create_map() that races with this unmap operates
  on a new map object with its own sg_table; the two do not share state.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 drivers/nvme/host/pci.c |  2 --
 lib/io_dmabuf_token.c   | 12 +++++-------
 2 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/nvme/host/pci.c b/drivers/nvme/host/pci.c
index 01cb74ec81b6..d8248d3222fb 100644
--- a/drivers/nvme/host/pci.c
+++ b/drivers/nvme/host/pci.c
@@ -2470,8 +2470,6 @@ static void nvme_dmabuf_token_unmap(struct io_dmabuf_token *token,
 	struct nvme_dmabuf_map *map = container_of(map_base,
 						struct nvme_dmabuf_map, base);
 
-	dma_resv_assert_held(token->dmabuf->resv);
-
 	dma_buf_unmap_attachment(data->attach, map->sgt, token->dir);
 	kfree(map->dma_list);
 }
diff --git a/lib/io_dmabuf_token.c b/lib/io_dmabuf_token.c
index 177321f6b2e9..46442df77a88 100644
--- a/lib/io_dmabuf_token.c
+++ b/lib/io_dmabuf_token.c
@@ -65,7 +65,6 @@ static void io_dmabuf_map_release_work(struct work_struct *work)
 					         release_work);
 	struct io_dmabuf_fence *fence = map->fence;
 	struct io_dmabuf_token *token = map->token;
-	struct dma_buf *dmabuf = token->dmabuf;
 
 	/* the release path must wait for fences */
 	if (WARN_ON_ONCE(refcount_read(&token->refs) == 0))
@@ -75,15 +74,14 @@ static void io_dmabuf_map_release_work(struct work_struct *work)
 	refcount_inc(&token->refs);
 
 	/*
-	 * There are no more requests using the map, we can signal the fence.
-	 * It should be done before taking the resv lock as someone could be
-	 * waiting for the fence while holding the lock.
+	 * Signal first so that GPU blits and other resv waiters are unblocked
+	 * before we attempt any further work. dma_buf_unmap_attachment() does
+	 * not require the reservation lock (only map_attachment does), so we
+	 * do not take it here — taking it would deadlock against any path that
+	 * holds the resv while waiting for this fence (e.g. KFD restore).
 	 */
 	dma_fence_signal(&fence->base);
-
-	dma_resv_lock(dmabuf->resv, NULL);
 	token->dev_ops->unmap(token, map);
-	dma_resv_unlock(dmabuf->resv);
 
 	dma_fence_put(&fence->base);
 	percpu_ref_exit(&map->refs);
-- 
2.43.0

